name: FZ25
description: The all-new bike has been developed with a newly designed air-cooled, 249 cc, 4-stroke, SOHC, 2-valve, single-cylinder, high-torque fuel-injected engine on a lightweight frame (152 Kgs) enabling the joy of control as the rider intends.

name: Black Yamaha YZF R15
description: The original supersport is back! Born of Yamaha’s racing DNA that shaped legends like M1, The R1 and the R-series, the all-new YZF R15 powered with Dual Channel ABS is max powerhouse of 18.6 PS that brings track experience to the streets.

name: Royal Enfield 650
description: The Royal Enfield 650 twins yet again lead the sales in the performance bike segment and in February 2022 they registered sales of 2469 units combined.

name: Yamaha YZF R1
description: Yamaha is the leading manufacturer of motorcycles, scooters, fishing boats, utility boats and a host of other motorized products. Yamaha, the manufacturer of the finest 4-stroke motorcycles in the world, has an exquisite range of bikes on offer.

name: Yamaha VMAX
description: VMax is Yamaha’s legendary power-cruiser with a 1,679cc V4 engine producing 200.1 PS of power and 166.8 Nm of torque. It is a performance cruiser, with and intimidating look.

name: Yamaha YZF R1
description: The Yamaha YZF R1 was manufactured by Yamaha automobile company from 1998 to the present. It is a super sports bike. In 1998-1999, the YZF-R1 was launched with a redesigned compact Genesis engine that appears like a stacked gearbox.
